---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About - ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Kristian Bjornebraten - Infrastructure Engineer, Cloud Architect, and DevOps enthusiast" />
		<style>
			main {
				width: 720px;
				max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
				margin: auto;
				padding: 3em 1em;
			}
			.about-header {
				text-align: center;
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}
			.about-avatar {
				width: 180px;
				height: 180px;
				border-radius: 50%;
				border: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
				margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
			}
			.about-content {
				line-height: 1.8;
				font-size: 1.1rem;
				color: var(--color-text-main);
			}
			h1 {
				font-size: 2.5rem;
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
				color: var(--color-text-main);
			}
			.tagline {
				color: var(--color-text-muted);
				font-size: 1.1rem;
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
			}
			h2 {
				margin-top: 2.5rem;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				font-size: 1.4rem;
				color: var(--color-accent);
				border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
				padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
			}
			p {
				margin-bottom: 1.25em;
			}
			a {
				color: var(--color-accent);
				text-decoration: none;
			}
			a:hover {
				text-decoration: underline;
			}
			ul {
				margin-bottom: 1.5em;
				padding-left: 1.5em;
			}
			li {
				margin-bottom: 0.75em;
			}
			strong {
				color: var(--color-text-main);
				font-weight: 600;
			}
			.highlight {
				background: var(--color-bg-alt);
				padding: 1.5rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
				border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
				margin: 2rem 0;
			}
			.tech-tags {
				display: flex;
				flex-wrap: wrap;
				gap: 0.5rem;
				margin-top: 1rem;
			}
			.tech-tag {
				background: var(--color-bg-alt);
				color: var(--color-text-muted);
				padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
				border-radius: 20px;
				font-size: 0.85rem;
				border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="about-header">
				<img src="/avatar.png" alt="Kristian Bjornebraten" class="about-avatar" />
				<h1>Kristian Bjornebraten</h1>
				<p class="tagline">Infrastructure Engineer · Cloud Architect · DevOps Enthusiast</p>
			</div>

			<section class="about-content">
				<p>
					I am a consultant and engineer with <strong>13 years of experience in IT</strong>. Throughout my career, 
					I have built extensive knowledge across complex IT infrastructure. In recent years, I have specialised in 
					cloud technology, DevOps, Infrastructure as Code, operations, application management, and technical leadership.
				</p>

				<div class="highlight">
					Outside of work, I spend my evenings vibe coding with headphones on and coffee in hand. 
					I build side projects like <a href="https://tidwerk.com">TidWerk</a> and explore the 
					<strong>MCP server</strong> ecosystem to see how AI agents can improve developer workflows. 
					Yes, I am that kind of nerd.
				</div>

				<h2>What I Do</h2>
				<p>
					I work as an Infrastructure Engineer, Technical Architect, and Delivery Manager. My focus is on 
					strengthening enterprise cloud platforms in Azure. As an architect, I design, develop, and troubleshoot 
					solutions that ensure secure and efficient communication, both within Azure and between cloud and 
					on-premises systems.
				</p>
				<p>
					I implement solutions that meet strict security and scalability requirements while ensuring compliance 
					with zone models and policies. As Delivery Manager, I take responsibility for delivering cloud-based 
					solutions with emphasis on time management, cost efficiency, and alignment with business objectives.
				</p>
				<p>
					Through agile methodologies and DevOps best practices, I optimise processes and strengthen teams to 
					deliver reliable solutions that meet customer needs.
				</p>

				<h2>Experience</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Technical Architect:</strong> Designed cloud architecture and hybrid solutions with focus on security, scalability, and compliance</li>
					<li><strong>Infrastructure Engineer:</strong> Built and maintained enterprise Azure platforms with automated provisioning and monitoring</li>
					<li><strong>Delivery Manager:</strong> Led delivery of cloud solutions using agile methods and DevOps practices</li>
					<li><strong>Platform Engineer:</strong> Developed and tested Terraform code, contributed to architecture decisions and technical assessments</li>
					<li><strong>Tech Lead:</strong> Led infrastructure teams and managed hybrid platforms across multiple environments</li>
					<li><strong>IaC Developer:</strong> Built Terraform solutions for critical infrastructure in regulated industries</li>
					<li><strong>Cloud Operator:</strong> Managed Azure operations with focus on continuous improvement</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Tech Stack</h2>
				<p>I work primarily with:</p>
				<div class="tech-tags">
					<span class="tech-tag">Azure</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">Terraform</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">Kubernetes</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">DevOps</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">TypeScript</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">Svelte</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">Python</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">Go</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">CI/CD</span>
					<span class="tech-tag">MCP Servers</span>
				</div>

				<h2>How I Work</h2>
				<p>
					I am productive, service-minded, analytical, and detail-oriented. I work in a structured and 
					goal-oriented manner to ensure tasks are completed in line with both technical and business expectations. 
					Whether I am designing enterprise infrastructure or working on personal projects late at night, 
					I bring the same level of dedication and curiosity.
				</p>

				<h2>Connect</h2>
				<p>
					I am always open to discussing cloud architecture, DevOps practices, or the latest in AI-assisted development. 
					Have a look at my <a href="/blog">blog</a> for thoughts on tech, or reach out if you want to collaborate.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
